{
  "text": "Novel mesoporous silica nanoparticles were efficiently loaded with chlorhexidine (CHX) which is generally used as antimicrobial agent in dentistry; they were synthesized with an average particle diameter of 140 nm and pore size of around 2.5 nm. Nano-CHX core-shell nanoparticles exhibited promising antimicrobial activity against critical oral pathogens including S. mutans, S. sobrinus, F. nucleatum, A. actinomycetem comitans and E. faecalis [CITATION_1] .",
